reviews.text: Had my 50th birthday party in the banquet hall. The event coordinator, Ms. Donna was great and very helpful in every detail. Staff set-up area and cleaned the area after the party. Our servers, Brittany and Ansley were wonderful and mindful of our guests needs. Food was great! Event area was beautiful! Staff was outstanding!!! Highly recommend using for any special event.
Hamburger came out raw, not medium, as order mashed potatoes cold . I truly hate to give them this review. I truly never had any problems with them before.

The atmosphere is nice ‚Äî clean, relaxed, and the space has a good vibe. But the food was average at best. I had the Black and Blue Burger, which was just okay. Nothing really stood out about it and it felt a bit underwhelming. The Broccoli Feta Garlic Salad was the best part of the meal. It was fresh and flavorful. Overall, the food did not live up to the atmosphere. Decent spot if you‚Äôre nearby but I would not go out of my way for it.

If you love aircraft and amazing food this is the stop for you. We enjoyed eating on the back porch. There was a helicopter that landed and a few planes thay took off on the runway. The food came out of the kitchen quick. Everyone left full and happy.

We only get back to GA about once a year and there's two places we try to go each time, our fave BBQ place and Barnstormers. Unfortunately the experience here has not been up to its old standards the last few times.  During COVID they took away the Sunday country buffet and never brought it back.  The remaining limited menu just doesn't do justice to the country cooking roots of years past.  I had an undercooked burger and green beans that not only weren't southern style, but were just oily. They used to have a phenomenal dessert selection too, but no more.  On top of all that, we  waited about 45 minutes for our food after being seated. Sadly, we're taking this off our must do list.

detailedReviews.author: Jenn Hengstenberg
detailedReviews.text: We only get back to GA about once a year and there's two places we try to go each time, our fave BBQ place and Barnstormers. Unfortunately the experience here has not been up to its old standards the last few times.  During COVID they took away the Sunday country buffet and never brought it back.  The remaining limited menu just doesn't do justice to the country cooking roots of years past.  I had an undercooked burger and green beans that not only weren't southern style, but were just oily. They used to have a phenomenal dessert selection too, but no more.  On top of all that, we  waited about 45 minutes for our food after being seated. Sadly, we're taking this off our must do list.

detailedReviews.text: Great restaurant off the beaten path. It was our first visit, but definitely not our last!! Large portions, quiet, and really cool artifacts that had my kids intrigued!

detailedReviews.text: This place was great the have a outdoor area to sit and eat or for kids to run around and play. Across the grass there is a hangar that you can see a plane which is very nice! Usually there‚Äôs not a wait!

Wait staff were very attentive, but not to the point of annoying. A gem that I am glad that I found and I will be back.

detailedReviews.text: My family and I came for the first time today. Ansley A was our server. She was amazing and very friendly. The food tasted great. All was seasoned well. We will definitely be coming back.

detailedReviews.text: Hamburger came out raw, not medium, as order mashed potatoes cold . I truly hate to give them this review. I truly never had any problems with them before.

detailedReviews.author: A P
detailedReviews.text: We heard so many good things about this place so we decided to give it a try. Atmosphere was nice and the staff was friendly. Great concept where you can see the planes landing and taking off. Lovely place but we were not impressed with the food (at least what we ordered) my husband got the steak. He said it was cooked the way he asked  but it had a TON of fat. I mean over half the steak was nothing but fat. The salad was ok, a little warm. We both agreed the mashed potatoes with gravy and the fried pickles were the best part. I ordered a club sandwich with no cheese ( the waitress verified our order and had everything right) however when the food came out to had cheese. Sandwich was ok, nothing special about it or stood out.

detailedReviews.author: Sydney Young
detailedReviews.text: If you love aircraft and amazing food this is the stop for you. We enjoyed eating on the back porch. There was a helicopter that landed and a few planes thay took off on the runway. The food came out of the kitchen quick. Everyone left full and happy.

detailedReviews.author: Dexter Leach
detailedReviews.text: Donna and the team was awesome on our son's wedding rehearsal dinner!  Nothing but great things to say!  So, say no more!

detailedReviews.text:
This was my first visit but it will not be my last.  The food was good but the service was great. Ore server was very personable and just lots of fun.

detailedReviews.text: Great service, and pretty good food!  My only issue was that the baked potato was not at all fresh.  It's kind of a bummer because I was looking forward to enjoying it with my shrimp.

detailedReviews.author: Seth Sorano
detailedReviews.text: Great entertainment venue with a gift shop and restaurant inside a hanger. Food portions are a fairly good size and well-flavored. Everyone on staff was friendly and accommodating. Pretty cool to watch small aircraft take off and land on the runway just outside.

detailedReviews.author: Ashley Ponder
detailedReviews.text: Really cool place! We had lunch here with our 5 kids and really enjoyed the atmosphere. We got to sit and watch the planes come and go while eating a great meal. I highly recommend the buffalo chicken sandwich and onion rings. I‚Äôd love to go back!

detailedReviews.author: Rivers Ludden
detailedReviews.text: Visited here with a friend who lives in the area. They have great local beers, good food, and you can watch airplanes take off and land from the attached grass runway! They also have a small stage for live music out by the porch.

detailedReviews.author: Kathy Silva
detailedReviews.text: Great place.

detailedReviews.author: M Bor
detailedReviews.text: Our server Donna was super nice and everything was great!  Yummy food and good drinks.  We also enjoyed some planes flying in and out.  Plenty of room for parking (we rode Harleys in and minimal gravel).  Enjoyed some burgers and sides.
